{"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/anylayout\/makecache(subviews:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AnyLayout"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"title":"makeCache(subviews:)","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Layout\/AnyLayout.swift#L131","fileName":"AnyLayout.swift"},"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnyLayoutV9makeCache8subviewsAC0G0VAA0E8SubviewsV_tF","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"makeCache","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"subviews","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AnyLayout","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnyLayoutV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"text":"Subviews","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore6LayoutP8Subviewsa","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AnyLayout","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnyLayoutV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Cache","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnyLayoutV5CacheV"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AnyLayout\/makeCache(subviews:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Creates and initializes a cache for a layout instance.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"makeCache"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"subviews"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AnyLayout","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnyLayoutV","text":"AnyLayout"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/Subviews","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore6LayoutP8Subviewsa","text":"Subviews"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AnyLayout","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnyLayoutV","text":"AnyLayout"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AnyLayout\/Cache","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnyLayoutV5CacheV","text":"Cache"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"subviews","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A collection of proxy instances that represent the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"views that the container arranges. You can use the proxies in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"collection to get information about the subviews as you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calculate values to store in the cache."}]}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"anchor":"return-value","level":2,"text":"Return Value","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Storage for calculated data that you share among","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the methods of your custom layout container.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can optionally use a cache to preserve calculated values across","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calls to a layout container’s methods. Many layout types don’t need","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a cache, because OpenSwiftUI automatically reuses both the results of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calls into the layout and the values that the layout reads from its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"subviews. Rely on the protocol’s default implementation of this method","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if you don’t need a cache.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"However you might find a cache useful when:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The layout container repeats complex, intermediate calculations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"across calls like "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AnyLayout\/sizeThatFits(proposal:subviews:cache:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AnyLayout\/placeSubviews(in:proposal:subviews:cache:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"explicitAlignment(of:in:proposal:subviews:cache:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You might be able to improve performance by calculating values"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"once and storing them in a cache."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The layout container reads many "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LayoutValueKey","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" values from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"subviews. It might be more efficient to do that once and store the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"results in the cache, rather than rereading the subviews’ values before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"each layout call."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You want to maintain working storage, like temporary Swift arrays,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"across calls into the layout, to minimize the number of allocation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"events.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Only implement a cache if profiling shows that it improves performance.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Initialize-a-cache","text":"Initialize a cache"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implement the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"makeCache(subviews:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method to create a cache."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can add computed values to the cache right away, using information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"subviews"},{"type":"text","text":" input parameter, or you can do that later. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"methods of the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol that can access the cache"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the cache as an in-out parameter, which enables you to modify"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the cache anywhere that you can read it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use any storage type that makes sense for your layout"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"algorithm, but be sure that you only store data that you derive"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from the layout and its subviews (lazily, if possible). For this to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"work correctly, OpenSwiftUI needs to be able to call this method to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recreate the cache without changing the layout result."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you return a cache from this method, you implicitly define a type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for your cache. Be sure to either make the type of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cache"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parameters on your other "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol methods match, or use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a type alias to define the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AnyLayout\/Cache","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" associated type."}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Update-the-cache","text":"Update the cache"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the layout container or any of its subviews change, OpenSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calls the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AnyLayout\/updateCache(_:subviews:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method so you can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modify or invalidate the contents of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cache. The default implementation of that method calls the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"makeCache(subviews:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method to recreate the cache, but you can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"provide your own implementation of the update method to take an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"incremental approach, if appropriate."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Layout/Subviews":{"ti